        "name": "Natural Disguise",
        "subtype": "ability",
        "text": "The camoufleur can use their disguise kit to disguise a creature or object as natural flora. A creature gains a +2 item bonus to Stealth checks while in a natural environment until its next daily preparations or until its disguise is ruined, whichever comes first. An object in a natural environment can be found only by actively searching (using the Search activity while exploring or the Seek action in an encounter) and uses the camoufleur's Stealth DC.",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
